xperiences awaits.<br><br><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->","cost_includes":"Half Day City Tour ( ATLANTIS , BURJ AL ARAB, FUTURE MUSEUM, PALM JUMERAH PHOTO STOP ) \nBurj Khalifa with entrance to 124th floor (ATMOSPHERE LOUNGE WITH GOLD COFFEE) \nMarina Cruise with dinner\nDesert Safari, with Belly Dance and dinner \nDubai Frame \n1 hr Limo Ride  \nOne Way Mono Rail Ride  \nAbu Dhabi city tour with Ferari World Photo Stop Only ( If You Want Ferari Pass approx. 8000 to 0000 Per Person Extra ) \nAbu Dhabi Grand Mosque  \nBAPS Hindu Temple  \nReturn economy class airfare (EX BOM). \nReturn airport transfers Dubai \/\/ Ras Al Khaimah\/Abu Dhabi Airport depending as per flight details. \nHotel accommodation in 4 star Hotel as per selected options with daily breakfast provided by hotel. \nTotal 05 Dinners including on Marina cruise & Desert safari BBQ. \nTotal 05 Breakfast at hotel  \nSightseeing mentioned with standard \/\/ basic entrance tickets. \nUAE normal 30 Days single entry tourist visa charges. \nTravel insurance for specific period. \nAll tours & transfers on Private basis. \nTourism Dirham tax.","cost_excludes":"GST 5% (Government Tax) on total package cost \nPorterage (Coolie charges), laundry, wines & alcoholic beverages, telephone charges, shopping, all items of personal nature and also food and drinks not forming the part of the group menus. \nAny extra expense such as route change, Airline change, Date change, Accommodation facilities, etc incurred due to the unforeseen, unavoidable forced majeure circumstances during the tour \nAny unexpected cost arising due to natural calamities e.g. bad weather, landslides, road blockage, political disturbances (strikes), etc. (and has to be paid by\ntravelers directly on the spot) \nAny extra cost incurred on behalf of an individual due to illness, accident, hospitalization, or any personal emergency \nAnything not specifically mentioned in \u2018Tour Price Includes Column.","itineraries":[],"faqs":[{"title":"1. What is included in this package? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The package includes accommodation, airport transfers, city tours of Dubai and Abu Dhabi, desert safari with BBQ dinner, dhow cruise, and entry to selected attractions as per itinerary.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"2. How many days are recommended for this trip? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Usually 5 to 7 days are ideal to cover both Dubai and Abu Dhabi comfortably.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"3. Do I need a visa to travel to Dubai and Abu Dhabi? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes, Indian passport holders require a UAE tourist visa. Our team can assist you with visa arrangements.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"4. What are the must-see attractions in Dubai? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Burj Khalifa, Dubai Mall, Palm Jumeirah, Dubai Marina, Dubai Frame, and the Gold &amp; Spice Souks are among the top highlights.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"5. What are the highlights of Abu Dhabi included? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque, Ferrari World\/Yas Island, Heritage Village, and Abu Dhabi Corniche are commonly covered.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"}],"is_featured":false,"featured_image":{"width":374,"height":226,"file":"2025\/09\/dubai-with-abu-dhabi.png","filesize":182319,"sizes":{"medium":{"file":"dubai-with-abu-dhabi-300x181.png","width":300,"height":181,"filesize":79268,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/dubai-with-abu-dhabi-300x181.png"},"thumbnail":{"file":"dubai-with-abu-dhabi-150x150.png","width":150,"height":150,"filesize":36832,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/dubai-with-abu-dhabi-150x150.png"},"blog-sidebar-size":{"file":"dubai-with-abu-dhabi-100x100.png","width":100,"height":100,"filesize":8721,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/